[SN]TITLE[SN]
Elderly man dies in County Donegal house fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An 80-year-old man has died in a house fire in County Donegal.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The blaze broke out in his home in Cloghan near Fintown at around 14:00 on Thursday.
Fire crews attended the scene but the man, who lived alone, died a short time later.
His body has been taken to Letterkenny University Hospital for a post mortem examination. The cause of the fire is being investigated.
